<text>Three ships of the United States Navy have borne the name USS &quot;Reuben James&quot;. Reuben James was a boatswain&#x27;s mate who distinguished himself fighting the Barbary pirates.

* The first , a four-stack , was the first US Navy ship sunk by hostile action in the European Theatre in World War II.
* The second , a , escorted convoys during World War II.
* The third was an guided missile frigate.</text><links>
